  "instructions": {
    "L": [
      {
        "S": "Place 2 cups brown lentils in a fine-mesh strainer and rinse thoroughly under cold running water, picking out any stones or debris. Drain well. Dice 1 yellow onion and mince 4 cloves garlic and 1 tablespoon fresh ginger. Peel 1 sweet potato and 2 carrots. Dice the sweet potato into 1/2-inch cubes and slice the carrots into 1/4-inch rounds."
      },
      {
        "S": "Add the rinsed lentils, diced onion, minced garlic, grated ginger, sweet potato cubes, carrot rounds, 3 tablespoons curry powder, 1 teaspoon ground cumin, 1/2 teaspoon turmeric, 1/4 teaspoon ground cloves if using, 1/4 teaspoon cayenne pepper if using, 1 teaspoon kosher salt, 1/4 teaspoon black pepper, 1 (15 ounce) can petite diced tomatoes with their juices, 1 (15 ounce) can tomato sauce, and 3 cups vegetable broth to a 5 to 6 quart slow cooker. Stir well to combine, making sure the spices are evenly distributed."
      },
      {
        "S": "Place the lid on the slow cooker and cook on HIGH for 4 hours or LOW for 7 to 8 hours. The lentils should be tender and most of the liquid should be absorbed. Avoid lifting the lid during cooking, as this releases heat and extends cooking time."
      },
      {
        "S": "Shake the can of coconut milk well, then stir 1 (14 ounce) can full-fat coconut milk into the cooked lentils until fully incorporated. Squeeze in 1 to 2 tablespoons fresh lime juice, starting with 1 tablespoon. Taste and adjust seasoning with additional salt (up to 1/2 teaspoon more), a pinch more curry powder, or a dash of cayenne pepper for heat as desired."
      },
      {
        "S": "Spoon about 1 cup of the lentil curry over 1 cup of cooked basmati or jasmine rice in a bowl. Top with finely diced red onion, fresh chopped cilantro or sliced green onions, and a lime wedge on the side. Serve with warm naan bread if desired."
      }
    ]
  },
  "notes": {
    "L": [
      {
        "S": "Gluten-Free: This recipe is naturally gluten-free as written. Verify that curry powder, vegetable broth, and canned tomato products are certified gluten-free. If serving with naan, use gluten-free naan."
      },
      {
        "S": "Dairy-Free and Vegan: This recipe is naturally vegan and dairy-free as written."
      },
      {
        "S": "Storage: Store the lentil curry (without rice) in airtight containers in the refrigerator for up to 5 days. The curry thickens as it cools - thin with a splash of broth or water when reheating."
      },
      {
        "S": "Freezer: Freeze the lentil curry (without rice) in portioned containers or freezer bags for up to 3 months. Thaw overnight in the refrigerator and reheat on the stovetop or microwave. Cook rice fresh when serving."
      },
      {
        "S": "Lentil type matters: Brown or green lentils hold their shape best in the slow cooker. Do not substitute red or yellow lentils - they will disintegrate into mush over this cooking time."
      },
      {
        "S": "Coconut milk: Full-fat coconut milk is essential for the creamy texture. Light coconut milk will produce a thinner, less rich result."
      },
      {
        "S": "Instant Pot adaptation: Cook on Manual or Pressure Cook HIGH for 15 minutes with a natural pressure release of 10 minutes."
      }
    ]
  },
